Did running through the troubleshooting info and doc at https://community.se.com/t5/Geo-SCADA-Knowledge-Base/Virtual-ViewX-Setup/ba-p/278269 come up with anything?


If I were sat infront of your machine this is the order of things I'd check to see what fails, assuming you're running dynamic users, and the bits in brackets afterwards are the hints to check if something doesn't happen


1. Delete all of the dynamic users in the local/AD security database, and check they're recreated when the users log into VVx (this makes sure the context that the Thinfinity VVx service runs under has permissions to create users, and the service knows the account passwords)

2. Check in Task Manager under the Users tab that the user is logged in but instantly shows disconnected which is normal (this makes sure the dynamic users have RDP access to the local machine, and credentials are good/known)

3. Check in Task Manager under details that ViewX process runs under the defined user account (checks that the user account for running ViewX has the right permissions/policies and credentials are known, which you can also check using the runas feature under a normal account)


If all that is happening then the fundamentals are in place. I haven't had to work with malfunctioning VVx too much to get a gut feeling yet on what the instant error returns and spinning wheels really mean to pinpoint specific areas to check.
